g.text: A traditional new year custom is to name the years by one of 12 animals in their zodiac cycle.In 2017, we ushered in the year of the Rooster on January, 28th. Every 12 years there is a Rooster year, beginning at Chinese New Year. A year of the Rooster always comes after a Monkey year and before a Dog year.Years of the Rooster include 1933, 1945, 1957, 1969, 1981, 1993, 2005, 2017, and 2029.
